ions, Lies, and ''Baron Munchausen's Narrative''|journal=Modern Philology|date=May 2012|volume=109|issue=4|pages=483–509|doi=10.1086/665538|jstor=10.1086/665538}} *{{citation|last=Knight|first=Lester N.|title=The Story of Peter Pan; Baron Munchausen: Eighteen Truly Tall Tales by Raspe and Others by Raspe|journal=The Reading Teacher|volume=27|issue=1|date=October 1973|pages=117, 119|jstor=20193416}} *{{citation|first=Pavel|last=Košatka|title=Komplexní recenze nového muzikálového hitu "Baron Prášil"|work=Muzical.cz|date=1 March 2010|url=http://www.musical.cz/recenze-reportaze/komplexni-recenze-noveho-muzikaloveho-hitu-baron-prasil/|accessdate=4 January 2015|language=Czech}} *{{Cite ADB|23|1|5|Münchhausen, Hieronimus Karl Friedrich Freiherr von|Krause, Karl Ernst Hermann|ADB:Münchhausen, Hieronymus Freiherr von (Erzähler)|ref=CITEREFKrause1886}} *{{citation|last=Lefebvre|first=Thierry|chapter=''A Trip to the Moon'': A Composite Film|pages=49–64|editor-last=Solomon|editor-first=Matthew|title=Fantastic Voyages of the Cinematic Imagination: Georges Méliès's Trip to the Moon|year=2011|publication-place=Albany, NY|publisher=State University of New York Press|isbn=978-1-4384-3581-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YNQ0-MPMzG0C&pg=PA60}} *{{citation|last=Levi|first=Claudia|chapter=Georgia Augustus University of Göttingen|editor1-last=Summerfield|editor1-first=Carol J.|editor2-first=Mary Elizabeth|editor2-last=Devine|title=International Dictionary of University Histories|location=Chicago|publisher=Fitzroy Dearborn Publishers|year=1998|pages=177–180|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tntEAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA177|isbn=978-1-134-26217-5}} *{{citation|last1=Meadow|first1=Roy|last2=Lennert|first2=Thomas|title=Munchausen Syndrome by Proxy or Polle Syndrome: Which Term is Correct?|journal=Pediatrics|volume=74|issue=4|date=October 1984|pages=554–556|pmid=6384913}} *{{citation|last1=Mitchell|first1=Alex|last2=McGee|first2=Kevin|chapter=Designing Storytelling Games That Encourage ''Narrative'' Play|pages=98–108|editor1-last=Iurgel|editor1-first=Ido|editor2-first=Nelson|editor2-last=Zagalo|editor3-first=Paolo|editor3-last=Petta|title=Interactive Storytelling: Second Joint International Conference on Interactive Digital Storytelling, ICIDS 2009, Guimarães, Portugal, December 9-11, 2009: Proceedings|location=Berlin|publisher=Springer|year=2009|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8_QKE9bSUYQC&pg=PA98|isbn=978-3-642-10642-2}} *{{citation|last=Nagle|first=Tobias|chapter=Projecting Desire, Rewriting Cinematic Memory: Gender and German Reconstruction in Michael Haneke's ''Fraulein''|editor-last=Grundmann|editor-first=Roy|title=A Companion to Michael Haneke|location=Chichester, West Sussex|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|year=2010|pages=263–278|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4VXkqzmaB4IC&pg=PA269|isbn=978-1-4443-2061-9}} *{{citation|author=NASA|authorlink=NASA|title=14014 Munchhausen (1994 AL16)|url=http://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=14014|work=JPL Small-Body Database Browser|year=2013|accessdate=3 February 2015}} *{{citation|last=Nietzsche|first=Friedrich|others=trans. and ed. Walter Kaufmann|title=Basic Writings of Nietzsche|location=New York|publisher=Modern Library|year=2000|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1dLQ-XiilEIC&pg=PA218|isbn=978-0-307-41769-5}} *{{citation|last=Olry|first=R.|title=Baron Munchhausen and the Syndrome Which Bears His Name: History of an Endearing Personage and of a Strange Mental Disorder|journal=Vesalius|date=June 2002|volume=VIII|issue=1|pages=53–57|url=http://www.bium.univ-paris5.fr/ishm/vesalius/VESx2002x08x01.pdf|accessdate=2 January 2015}} *{{citation|last1=Orly|first1=Régis|first2=Duane E.|last2=Haines|chapter=Historical and Literary Roots of Münchhausen Syndromes: As Intriguing as the Syndromes Themselves|pages=123–142|editor1-last=Finger|editor1-first=Stanley|editor2-first=François|editor2-last=Boller|editor3-first=Anne|editor3-last=Stiles|title=Literature, Neurology, and Neuroscience|location=Burlington|publ